OPTIONAL
SYNOPSIS
        int pg_listen(string channel, string fun)
        int pg_listen(string channel, string fun, string|object obj,
                       mixed extra, ...)
        int pg_listen(string channel, closure cl, mixed extra, ...)

DESCRIPTION
        Start listening on a channel on the database connection for the current object.
        Assigns the callback function <fun>/<cl> with the optional <extra> parameters
        to it. When a PostgreSQL NOTIFY event for the <channel> is received from the
        database, the callback is invoked.

        The callback function receives the channel name as the first argument, and 
        the notify payload (if any) as the second argument. If there is no payload,
        the second argument is 0.
        
        void <callback>(string channel, string|int payload [, mixed extra...])

        Return 1 on success.

        The function is available only if the driver is compiled with
        PostgreSQL support. In that case, __PGSQL__ is defined.

        The efun triggers a privilege violation ("pgsql", "pg_listen").

HISTORY
        Added in LDMud 3.6.8.

SEE ALSO
        pgsql(C), pg_connect(E), pg_query(E), pg_unlisten(E),
        privilege_violation(M)
